## Math Quality

<definition title="Fourier Transform">
The Fourier transform of a function <m>f \in L^1(\mathbb{R})</m> is

<math number="true" label="eq:fourier">
\hat{f}(\xi) = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} f(x)\, e^{-2\pi i x \xi}\, dx
</math>
</definition>

<theorem title="Parseval's Theorem">
For <m>f, g \in L^2(\mathbb{R})</m>, the Fourier transform is an isometry:

<math>
\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} f(x)\,\overline{g(x)}\,dx
  = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \hat{f}(\xi)\,\overline{\hat{g}(\xi)}\,d\xi
</math>
</theorem>

---

## Ecosystem

<timeline>
  <event date="2023-01" title="v1.0 — First Release">
  Markdown + KaTeX. 8 features. 400 GitHub stars day one.
  </event>
  <event date="2023-09" title="v3.0 — Diagrams">
  18 diagram types via custom SVG layout engine. No Mermaid dependency.
  </event>
  <event date="2024-03" title="v5.0 — Components">
  `<component>` system with props and slots. Plugin API v1.
  </event>
  <event date="2024-11" title="v7.0 — Live Collaboration">
  Real-time multi-user editing via CRDT. WebSocket backend optional.
  </event>
  <event date="2025-06" title="v8.0 — Infinity Architecture">
  Full `<Tag>` unification. Removed all legacy `@directive` syntax.
  Virtual DOM diffing. 50k-line document support.
  </event>
</timeline>

